"
  Combine elements in a list using addition.

  If the list is empty or has only a single element,
  this is the list itself.
  
  Otherwise, this is a single-element list containing
  the result of combining the elements of the list using
  addition.
" => (
  usage examples = [
    [].sum == []
    [3].sum == [3]
    [1,1].sum == [2]
    [1,1,1].sum == [3]
    [1,1,1,1].sum == [4]
    [2,3,4,5].sum == [14]  
  ]
) => list.combine using binary operator(.+)